04741nam a22007335i 9780823292936DE-B159720220329044247.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220329t20222006nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232929367 a10.1515/97808232929362doi  a(DE-B1597)566116  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aPHI0220002bisacsh04aThe Experience of God :bA Postmodern Response /ced. by Barbara Wall, Kevin Hart. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2022] 4c©2006  a1 online resource (278 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aPerspectives in Continental Philosophy00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Experience of God and the Axiology of the Impossible -- t2 Experience of God: A Response to John D. Caputo -- t3 ‘‘A World Split Open’’?: Experience and Feminist Theologies -- t4 A Womanist Experience: A Response to Kristine Culp -- t5 The Experience of the Kingdom of God -- t6 Faith and the Conditions of Possibility of Experience: A Response to Kevin Hart -- t7 Liturgy and Coaffection -- t8 A Response to Jean-Yves Lacoste -- t9 When God Hides His Face: The Inexperience of God0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book provides a series of approaches to the ancient question of whether and how God is a matter of “experience,” or, alternately, to what extent the notion of experience can be true to itself if it does not include God. On the one hand, it seems impossible to experience God: the deity does not offer Himself to sense experience. On the other hand, there have been mystics who have claimed to have encountered God. The essays in this collection seek to explore the topic again, drawing insights from phenomenology, theology, literature, and feminism. Throughout, this stimulating collection maintains a strong connection with concrete rather than abstract approaches to God. The contributors: Michael F. Andrews, Jeffrey Bloechl, John D. Caputo, Kristine Culp, Kevin Hart, Kevin L. Hughes, Jean-Yves Lacoste, Crystal Lucky, Renee McKenzie, Kim Paffenroth, Michael Purcell, Michael J. Scanlon, O.S.A., James K. A. Smith.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aBloechl, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaputo, John D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCulp, Kristine A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Kevin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLacoste, Jean-Yves, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcKenzie, Renee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPurcell, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScanlon, Michael J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, James K. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWall, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWall, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823292936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823292936/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSH